# WordPress Embed: Sticky Fix & Breakout

## position:sticky inside WordPress

CSS `position: sticky` breaks when ANY ancestor has `overflow: hidden/auto/scroll`. WordPress themes always have these. Add this JS snippet to walk up the DOM and clear them:

```javascript
var scrolly = document.getElementById('fld-scrolly-ID');
if (scrolly) {
  var el = scrolly.parentElement;
  while (el && el !== document.documentElement) {
    var ov = window.getComputedStyle(el).overflow;
    if (ov === 'hidden' || ov === 'auto' || ov === 'scroll') {
      el.style.overflow = 'visible';
    }
    var ovX = window.getComputedStyle(el).overflowX;
    var ovY = window.getComputedStyle(el).overflowY;
    if (ovX === 'hidden') el.style.overflowX = 'visible';
    if (ovY === 'hidden') el.style.overflowY = 'visible';
    el = el.parentElement;
  }
}
```

## Full-width breakout

WordPress content sits inside a max-width container. Force full-width with:

```css
.fld-article {
  position: relative !important;
  width: 100vw !important;
  left: 50% !important;
  margin-left: -50vw !important;
}
```

## CSS conflict prevention

- Prefix all classes with `fld-` to avoid WordPress theme collisions
- Use `!important` on layout-critical properties (display, position, width, flex)
- Use box-sizing reset on the wrapper: `.fld-article *, .fld-article *::before, .fld-article *::after { box-sizing: border-box !important; }`
